==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/dɛrəlɪkt/}}
*{{SAMPA|/dEr@lIkt/}}

===Etymology===
[[Latin]] ''derelictus'' [[past participle]] of ''derelinquere'' 'forsake, abandon' from ''de'' + ''relinquere'' 'leave, forsake'.

===Adjective===
{{en-adj-more}}

#Abandonded, forsaken; (of ship) abandonded at sea; dilapidated, neglected.
#: ''There was a '''derelict''' ship on the island.''
#Negligent in performing a duty.

====Synonyms====
'''abandonded'''
* [[abandoned]]

